node.text:
Switzerland's cliff walk is for thrill-seekers only via @michelphotographych 🇨🇭Get your photos posted in our account, apply for a feature visiting tourfervor.com 👉🏼 the link is in our bio: @tourfervor

Would you be brave enough to walk through this high walkway suspended from a rocky mountainside, with peak & valley views, accessed by gondola?

About 300 meters long. It takes just 10-15 minutes to walk it in one direction, photo stops included. If you want to walk it both ways, count about half an hour for your visit.

The First Cliff Walk in Switzerland wraps around the mountains of Grindelwald and is a breathtaking experience for those brave enough to embark on the hike up the Bernese Alps. Most of the area is car free, First included. Grindelwald itself can be reached by car, but for nearly all other places you can travel by train and cable cars only.

Travel Tips: The easiest way to get to First Cliff Walk is by taking a 25-minutes gondola ride from Grindelwald to First. From there, it's just a short walk of 5 minutes to the Cliff Walk. You cannot drive up to First by car or by bus and hiking here from Grindelwald would take you several hours.

📽 @michelphotographych
📍Grindelwald, Switzerland
🎶 Ben Pellow - Roslyn

Why have pets when you can train wild macaws 🦜 Wanna see your pictures posted in our account? Apply for a feature on tourfervor.com (link in my bio: @tourfervor)

They come every morning for food. In Spanish macaws are called guacamayas, these are native to Caracas Venezuela.

📽 TT bbitoslove
📍 Caracas, Venezuela

node.text:
Umbrella tree 🌳 Share your photos with us and we will post them in our account. Apply for a feature following the link in our bio: @tourfervor

How impressive is this holm oak? Known as the umbrella tree. Once a year two gardeners climb up into its crown on ladders, and for two weeks they prune the tree like a skirt as they meticulously trim it into shape. Its healing powers helped James Bond recuperate – Casino Royale.

📽 @brigrc
📍Villa del Balbianello, Como, Italy

node.text:
Wild ride 🐎 Get your photos posted in our account, apply for a feature visiting tourfervor.com 👉🏼 the link is in our bio: @tourfervor

Bareback riding is a form of horseback riding without a saddle. It requires skill, balance, and coordination, as the rider does not have any equipment to compensate for errors of balance or skill.

Proponents of bareback riding argue that riding in this fashion is natural, allows considerable communication with the horse, and improves a rider's balance. The drawbacks include a higher risk of injury due to an increased risk of falling off the horse, the potential to develop poor riding form, and the possibility of considerable discomfort to both horse and rider due to the absence of a supporting tree and any padding between the rider's seat bones and the horse's spine. Over time, it is more fatiguing to both horse and rider to ride bareback.

📽 @kerrikasem
🎶 Sting - Desert Rose (feat. Cheb Mami)
📍 Essaouira, Morocco

Dolomites in Italy 🇮🇹 We can post your content in our account. Check the link in our bio for more info: @tourfervor

Dolomites are just magical. Some tourists prefer to travel to the Dolomites during the summer, between May and September, when the weather is pleasantly warm and the mountains lively and colorful. Early spring, when crocuses, Alpine snowdrops and scented bushes of Daphne bloom through the melting snow, is equally beautiful.

📽 @rebe.twosoles
📍 Dolomites, Italy
